To enhance the visibility of imaging features and reduce noise, a multistep preprocessing pipeline was applied. Contrast Limited Adaptive Histogram Equalization (CLAHE) was employed to improve local contrast in dense tissue regions, followed by Gaussian blurring to suppress high-frequency noise, defined as:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
