				\begin{document}$$\:G\left(x,y\right)=\:1\:2\pi\:\sigma\:2\mathrm{exp}-x2+y2\:2\sigma\:2\:$$\end{document}

Where σ represents the standard deviation of the Gaussian distribution, subsequently, bilateral filtering was applied to preserve edge structures critical for mass detection, expressed as:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
